<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - REAR COVER, FLYWHEEL, and POWER STEERING GEAR DRIVE -
        Installation - Flexplate
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Flexplate</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, use new bolts to install flexplate.</para>
            </caution>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use anitseize, grease, or lubricants on flexplate bolts. Each has
                    an adverse effect on torque results.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2651338" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/d0732.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 488. Flexplate</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flexplate bolts, M10 x 77 (10)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Reinforcement ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Flexplate adapter hub</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Transmission side stamp (XMSN-SIDE)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the flexplate onto adapter hub and align hub over the crankshaft secondary flange
                dowel. Make sure the XMSN-SIDE stamp is facing toward the transmission.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install reinforcement ring and align all bolt holes. Make sure lip on outer circumference of
                ring is facing towards the transmission.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put two M10 x 77 bolts 180&#176; apart through reinforcement ring, flexplate, and adapter
                hub.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place entire flexplate assembly onto crankshaft. Hand tighten two bolts to hold assembly in
                place.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install eight remaining M10 x 77 flexplate mounting bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Snug all bolts in the sequence shown to 1 - 7 N&#183;m (12 - 60 lbf&#183;in).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Torque all bolts to the special torque and in the sequence shown .</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
